---
import DocsLayout from '../../../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';

const faqAccordionStyles = `.faq-accordion details {
  border-bottom: var(--border-width-thin) solid var(--color-border);
}

.faq-accordion details:first-child {
  border-top: var(--border-width-thin) solid var(--color-border);
}

.faq-accordion summary {
  display: flex;
  justify-content: space-between;
  align-items: center;
  padding: var(--size-m) 0;
  cursor: pointer;
  font-weight: var(--font-weight-medium);
  list-style: none;
}

.faq-accordion summary::-webkit-details-marker {
  display: none;
}

.faq-accordion summary::marker {
  display: none;
  content: "";
}

.faq-accordion details[open] summary icon-wc {
  transform: rotate(180deg);
}

.faq-accordion summary icon-wc {
  transition: transform var(--duration-fast) var(--ease-default);
  flex-shrink: 0;
  color: var(--color-text-muted);
}

.faq-accordion .faq-answer {
  padding-bottom: var(--size-m);
  color: var(--color-text-muted);
}`;

const faqGridStyles = `.faq-item h3 {
  font-size: var(--font-size-m);
  margin: 0 0 var(--size-xs) 0;
}

.faq-item p {
  color: var(--color-text-muted);
  margin: 0;
}`;
---

<DocsLayout
  title="FAQ Patterns"
  description="FAQ section patterns for landing pages and marketing sites. Accordion and grid layouts for displaying frequently asked questions."
  currentSection="examples"
>
  <nav class="breadcrumb" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
    <a href="/docs/patterns/">Patterns</a> / <a href="/docs/patterns/marketing/">Marketing</a> / <span aria-current="page">FAQ</span>
  </nav>

  <h1>FAQ Patterns</h1>
  <p class="lead">FAQ section patterns for landing pages and marketing sites. Clear, accessible layouts for answering common customer questions.</p>

  <section>
    <h2>Overview</h2>
    <layout-text>
      <p>FAQ sections help users find answers quickly without contacting support. These patterns use native HTML elements like <code>&lt;details&gt;</code> and <code>&lt;summary&gt;</code> for the accordion variant, ensuring accessibility and no-JavaScript functionality.</p>
      <p><strong>Key features:</strong></p>
      <ul>
        <li>Native <code>&lt;details&gt;</code>/<code>&lt;summary&gt;</code> for accordion behavior</li>
        <li>No JavaScript required for expand/collapse</li>
        <li>Responsive grid layout for two-column variant</li>
        <li>Accessible keyboard navigation built-in</li>
        <li>Smooth CSS transitions for accordion indicator</li>
        <li>SEO-friendly structured content</li>
      </ul>
    </layout-text>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Accordion</h2>
    <layout-text>
      <p>The classic FAQ accordion pattern using native <code>&lt;details&gt;</code> and <code>&lt;summary&gt;</code> elements. Each question expands to reveal its answer, keeping the page compact while allowing users to explore topics of interest.</p>
    </layout-text>

    <browser-window
      src="/docs/patterns/demos/faq-accordion.html"
      url="https://vanilla-breeze.dev/faq-accordion"
      title="FAQ Accordion"
      shadow>
    </browser-window>

    <code-block language="html" label="FAQ accordion with details/summary">&lt;div class="faq-accordion"&gt;
  &lt;details&gt;
    &lt;summary&gt;
      &lt;span&gt;What is Vanilla Breeze?&lt;/span&gt;
      &lt;icon-wc name="chevron-down" size="sm"&gt;&lt;/icon-wc&gt;
    &lt;/summary&gt;
    &lt;div class="faq-answer"&gt;
      &lt;p&gt;Vanilla Breeze is a lightweight CSS framework built on modern web standards. It uses semantic HTML, custom elements, and design tokens to help you build beautiful interfaces without a build step or JavaScript framework.&lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/details&gt;
  &lt;details&gt;
    &lt;summary&gt;
      &lt;span&gt;How do I get started?&lt;/span&gt;
      &lt;icon-wc name="chevron-down" size="sm"&gt;&lt;/icon-wc&gt;
    &lt;/summary&gt;
    &lt;div class="faq-answer"&gt;
      &lt;p&gt;Getting started is easy. You can include Vanilla Breeze via CDN with a single link tag, or install it via npm for more customization options. Check out our Getting Started guide for step-by-step instructions.&lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/details&gt;
  &lt;details&gt;
    &lt;summary&gt;
      &lt;span&gt;Is Vanilla Breeze free to use?&lt;/span&gt;
      &lt;icon-wc name="chevron-down" size="sm"&gt;&lt;/icon-wc&gt;
    &lt;/summary&gt;
    &lt;div class="faq-answer"&gt;
      &lt;p&gt;Yes, Vanilla Breeze is completely free and open source under the MIT license. You can use it in personal and commercial projects without any restrictions.&lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/details&gt;
  &lt;!-- More items... --&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;</code-block>

    <h3>Required CSS</h3>
    <layout-text>
      <p>Add these styles for the accordion appearance and animated chevron indicator:</p>
    </layout-text>

    <code-block language="css" label="FAQ accordion styles">{faqAccordionStyles}</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Two-Column Grid</h2>
    <layout-text>
      <p>A grid layout that displays all FAQ items at once, arranged in two columns on wider screens. Uses <code>&lt;layout-grid&gt;</code> with a minimum column width of 400px for automatic responsive behavior.</p>
    </layout-text>

    <browser-window
      src="/docs/patterns/demos/faq-two-column.html"
      url="https://vanilla-breeze.dev/faq-two-column"
      title="FAQ Two Column"
      shadow>
    </browser-window>

    <code-block language="html" label="Two-column FAQ grid">&lt;layout-grid data-min="400px" data-gap="xl" class="faq-grid"&gt;
  &lt;article class="faq-item"&gt;
    &lt;layout-stack data-gap="xs"&gt;
      &lt;h3&gt;What is Vanilla Breeze?&lt;/h3&gt;
      &lt;p&gt;A lightweight CSS framework built on modern web standards. Semantic HTML, custom elements, and design tokens without a build step.&lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;/layout-stack&gt;
  &lt;/article&gt;
  &lt;article class="faq-item"&gt;
    &lt;layout-stack data-gap="xs"&gt;
      &lt;h3&gt;How do I get started?&lt;/h3&gt;
      &lt;p&gt;Include Vanilla Breeze via CDN with a single link tag, or install via npm for more customization options.&lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;/layout-stack&gt;
  &lt;/article&gt;
  &lt;article class="faq-item"&gt;
    &lt;layout-stack data-gap="xs"&gt;
      &lt;h3&gt;Is Vanilla Breeze free to use?&lt;/h3&gt;
      &lt;p&gt;Yes, it's completely free and open source under the MIT license for personal and commercial projects.&lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;/layout-stack&gt;
  &lt;/article&gt;
  &lt;!-- More items... --&gt;
&lt;/layout-grid&gt;</code-block>

