  <section>
    <h2>Usage Notes</h2>
    <layout-text>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Accordion vs Grid:</strong> Use accordion for longer FAQ lists (6+ items) to save space. Use grid for shorter lists where scanning all questions at once is helpful.</li>
        <li><strong>Native details/summary:</strong> The accordion uses native HTML elements, providing keyboard navigation and screen reader support without JavaScript.</li>
        <li><strong>No JavaScript required:</strong> The accordion expand/collapse works purely with HTML and CSS. The chevron rotation uses CSS transitions.</li>
        <li><strong>SEO structured data:</strong> Consider adding <a href="https://schema.org/FAQPage">FAQPage schema markup</a> for rich search results. Wrap your FAQ section with <code>itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/FAQPage"</code>.</li>
        <li><strong>Question length:</strong> Keep questions concise (under 80 characters). Move complex details to the answer section.</li>
        <li><strong>Answer formatting:</strong> Use paragraphs, lists, and links within answers. Avoid deeply nested content.</li>
        <li><strong>Open by default:</strong> Add the <code>open</code> attribute to a <code>&lt;details&gt;</code> element to have it expanded on page load.</li>
        <li><strong>Grouping:</strong> For large FAQ lists, consider grouping questions by category with section headings.</li>
      </ul>
    </layout-text>
  </section>

